a.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2025%2F05%2FMervin-Feature-image-2025-05-27T173926.242-1748347780-150x79.jpg%20150w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-439735%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22628%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%20class%3D%5C%22wp-element-caption%5C%22%3EIt%20would%20take%20the%20Arabian%20Sea%20months%20together%20to%20return%20to%20its%20normal%20ecosystem.%20Picture%20source%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fassets.telegraphindia.com%2Ftelegraph%2F2ea9b5e9-16a9-489a-a0b9-3c9fcb5c5b8d.jpg%5C%22%3ETelegraph%20India%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20long-term%20studies%20by%20the%20National%20Oceanic%20and%20Atmospheric%20Administration%20(NOAA)%20and%20the%20International%20Tanker%20Owners%20Pollution%20Federation%20(ITOPF)%2C%20oil%20spills%20can%20leave%20persistent%20residues%20in%20marine%20sediments%2C%20disrupt%20food%20chains%2C%20and%20reduce%20biodiversity%20for%20years%20%E2%80%94%20even%20decades.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ELet%E2%80%99s%20look%20at%20one%20stark%20example%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3Cbr%3EAfter%20the%20Exxon%20Valdez%20oil%20spill%20in%20Alaska%20(1989)%2C%20scientists%20found%20that%20oil%20residues%20remained%20in%20coastal%20sediments%20and%20mussel%20beds%20more%20than%2025%20years%20later.%20Some%20species%20of%20fish%20and%20seabirds%20in%20the%20region%20never%20fully%20rebounded.%20While%20the%20surface%20appeared%20clean%20within%20months%2C%20ecological%20scars%20lingered%20deep%20below.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20tropical%20waters%20like%20the%20Arabian%20Sea%2C%20warmer%20temperatures%20may%20speed%20up%20the%20natural%20breakdown%20of%20oil%20through%20microbial%20activity.%20But%20that%20only%20helps%20with%20lighter%20oil%20components.%20Heavier%20fuels%20like%20furnace%20oil%20%E2%80%94%20the%20kind%20leaked%20off%20Kochi%20%E2%80%94%20are%20sticky%2C%20slow%20to%20degrade%2C%20and%20more%20likely%20to%20sink%20and%20persist.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ECoastal%20ecosystems%20like%20mangro